, and sexuality in American culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAfrican American churchesxDoctrines. 0aAfrican American churchesxPolitical activity. 0aSexxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBest, Wallace, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraxton, Brad R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Michael Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamp, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, Monica A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEibach, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Serene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunior, Nyasha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoultrie, Monique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPowery, Luke A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, Melynda J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPurdie Greenaway, Valerie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSavage, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSorett, Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSorett, Josef, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWalton, Jonathan Lee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/sore1883240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231547772423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/